<p>Testicular cancer is a relatively rare type of cancer, accounting for just 1% of all cancers that occur in men.</p>

<p>Around 2,300 men are diagnosed with testicular cancer each year in the UK.</p>

<p>Testicular cancer is unusual compared with other cancers because it tends to affect younger men.</p>

